[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:56,067 --> 00:02:02,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

24
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,733
Ow--[MUFFLED SCREAM]

25
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,733
[THUNDER ROARS]

26
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,300
[WATER SPLASHES]

27
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:11,667
Did you hear that?

28
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:13,733
Hear what?

29
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:17,667
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,733
Missy?

31
00:02:19,967 --> 00:02:21,033
Missy!

32
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:31,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:41,600
[SARAH] Grace!

34
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,667
Excuse me.

35
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,000
Grace?

36
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:46,033
Oh!

37
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,467
Sir! Do you remember me?

38
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,900
I'm Sarah. Do you have any
information about my daughter?

39
00:02:54,767 --> 00:02:57,800
Why did they let
the kid wander off?

40
00:02:57,967 --> 00:03:01,367
There's a thunderstorm
and the waves are strong.

41
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,300
[BYSTANDER 1] I heard
it's not an accident.

42
00:03:05,433 --> 00:03:06,633
The kid might've
jumped into the sea.

43
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:08,567
[BYSTANDER 2] Seriously?
You think a kid would do that?

44
00:03:08,667 --> 00:03:10,300
It's definitely
not an accident.

45
00:03:10,467 --> 00:03:12,467
Who knows, it could
have been premeditated.

46
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,733
- That's right.
- Someone pushed her.

47
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:23,633
[BYSTANDERS MURMURING]

48
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,567
That must be her stuff.

49
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:33,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
[BYSTANDERS MURMURING]

50
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:46,167
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:35,200
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,500
[APPLAUSE]

53
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,800
Yes. Don't worry.
I will not miss my flight.

54
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:54,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
[APPLAUSE]

55
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,900
[HOST] Thank you, Section Narra.

56
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:57,867
I'll have everything ready
by then.

57
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:01,500
The grant is very
important to me.

58
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:04,067
Thank you.
Thank you so much.

59
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,767
Yes, I will.

60
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:06,600
Yes.

61
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:13,833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

62
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:19,567
Hey, why aren't you
in your costume?

63
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:22,433
Uh... I forgot.

64
00:05:22,567 --> 00:05:25,100
Oh, did you also forget
to take a shower?

65
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:26,833
- You stink.
- Yeah.

66
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:29,433
- You smell bad.
- Your clothes are dirty.

67
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,100
And you have lice too.

68
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:33,033
- Get out of here!
- Leave!

69
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:35,733
- I didn't do anything wrong!
- Stay away from us!

70
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:42,633
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
[CLAMORING]

71
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:45,867
[GRACE] I didn't do
anything wrong!

72
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,300
Just stay there!

73
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:54,733
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:05:54,833 --> 00:05:57,567
Kids, get ready.
You're up next.

75
00:05:57,667 --> 00:05:59,867
Hang on. Where's Grace?

76
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,967
We haven't seen her, ma'am.

77
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,933
She hasn't shown up.

78
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:04,867
[APPLAUSE]

79
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,633
That's your cue.
Do your best, okay? Go.

80
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:10,767
So, you're really leaving?

81
00:06:10,867 --> 00:06:12,000
Teacher Patty,
Happy Teacher's Day!

82
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:12,767
Thank you.

83
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,733
I'll be leaving for Hong Kong
next month.

84
00:06:18,667 --> 00:06:21,000
Are you sure about that?
Thank you, dear.

85
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:24,800
You really want to study
migratory birds?

86
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,067
Won't that be boring?

87
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,167
Thank you, dear.
Thank you, thank you.

88
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:30,300
I've always wanted
to study ornithology.

89
00:06:30,433 --> 00:06:32,500
I just didn't have the money.

90
00:06:32,633 --> 00:06:34,300
That's why I worked hard
on that proposal.

91
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:35,567
I'm glad it was approved.

92
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:37,233
Hey, Anna.

93
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:41,167
You also worked hard
to get a teaching license.

94
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:44,633
Are you saying the year
you spent here was for nothing?

95
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:48,033
I only became a teacher
to fund my studies.

96
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,867
I never planned on
doing it long-term.

97
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:50,867
Thank you.

98
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:58,033
That's a shame.
You're such a great teacher.

99
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:01,033
The kids listen to you.

100
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:03,100
They listen because
they're scared of you.

101
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:04,100
[GIGGLES]

102
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:08,867
But seriously, Anna,
the kids need us here.

103
00:07:11,567 --> 00:07:13,367
Have you talked to the principal
about this?

104
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:15,333
You know you're his favorite.

105
00:07:16,533 --> 00:07:19,200
I'll talk to him soon.
But he can't change my mind.

106
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:22,800
[PATTY] Thank you.
Thank you so much.

107
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:38,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

108
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:42,867
[STUDENT] Why did you force
me to give that?

109
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:48,833
- It's okay, dear.
- I didn't want to do that.

110
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:52,400
Let us give a round
of applause

111
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:55,400
for Section Acacia!

112
00:07:55,533 --> 00:08:01,500
[CHEERING, APPLAUSE]

113
00:08:01,633 --> 00:08:08,433
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

114
00:08:14,767 --> 00:08:17,200
Oh no! They're not in sync!

115
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,900
Classmates, follow me!

116
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,100
[TEACHER] Grace,
what are you doing?!

117
00:08:29,233 --> 00:08:32,633
[APPLAUSE]

118
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:35,767
[GROANS] Grace! You don't
even have a costume!

119
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:41,133
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]
[TEACHER GROANING]

120
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:45,433
[TEACHER GROANING] Aah!

121
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:48,400
My water just broke!

122
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,267
Ugh!

123
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,067
Aah!

124
00:08:54,200 --> 00:09:00,600
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]
[TEACHER CONTINUES GROANING]

125
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:01,933
[MAN] Call for help!

126
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:08,800
[CLAMORING CONTINUES]
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:18,433
[STUDENTS SHOUTING,
LAUGHING EXCITEDLY]

128
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:23,433
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

129
00:09:23,533 --> 00:09:27,667
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

130
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:33,767
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

131
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,033
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

132
00:09:51,233 --> 00:09:54,200
Mm. What are the five senses?

133
00:09:54,367 --> 00:09:58,767
Hearing, smelling,
tasting, um...

134
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,367
Common sense?

135
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:03,033
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

136
00:10:03,233 --> 00:10:04,200
Shh!

137
00:10:07,933 --> 00:10:10,233
I just taught you that
yesterday.

138
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:13,367
I want to go home.

139
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:21,800
"ACCEPTANCE LETTER"

140
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:25,300
"Booking Details
Booking Date: April 19, 2025

141
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:26,867
Passenger Details
Anna Grace Sarmiento"

142
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,333
[PHONE RINGING]

143
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:33,833
Hello?

144
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:41,133
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

145
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:45,033
That was fast. I guess
you only answer my calls.

146
00:10:45,133 --> 00:10:48,400
Auntie has something
important to tell you.

147
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:51,033
Charlie! Charlie, wait--

148
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:52,267
Hello?

149
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,667
Anna!

150
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,733
Mama.

151
00:10:54,867 --> 00:10:57,200
Why aren't you
answering my calls?

152
00:10:57,300 --> 00:11:00,067
Did you receive
your sister's invitation?

153
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:02,767
She sent it to your
email last week.

154
00:11:02,900 --> 00:11:04,433
Yes, I got it.

155
00:11:04,567 --> 00:11:06,533
So, when are you coming home?

156
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,667
I'm sorry, Ma.

157
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,633
I won't be able
to come home yet.

158
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:11,767
Huh?

159
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:12,800
Why?

160
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:15,400
I still have school.

161
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,900
You have school?

162
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,367
Are you taking up
your PhD?

163
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,800
No, I mean at an
elementary school.

164
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:24,700
I work there.

165
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,733
What happened?

166
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:29,867
I thought you work
as a research assistant

167
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,467
at a university?

168
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,467
It's a long story, Ma.

169
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:36,200
Can I tell you next time?

170
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:37,967
[SIGHS]

171
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:41,467
Anna, this is
a special occasion.

172
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:43,333
We must be complete.

173
00:11:43,467 --> 00:11:46,067
You haven't been home
in ages.

174
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:49,133
You need to be at
your sister's wedding.

175
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:55,167
Oh-- Oh, Princess, talk
to your sister.

176
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:57,433
If she doesn't want to come,
don't force her.

177
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,300
We'll be fine without her.

178
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:00,833
Oh my goodness.

179
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:02,400
Anna...

180
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:05,833
Please, for my sake.

181
00:12:05,967 --> 00:12:07,833
Come home.

182
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:11,133
We also have
to file the inn's income tax.

183
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,000
I need you here.

184
00:12:15,033 --> 00:12:17,333
What happened to the
accountant I hired?

185
00:12:17,467 --> 00:12:18,767
I fired them.

186
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:20,467
I don't like their attitude.

187
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:22,533
And besides,

188
00:12:22,667 --> 00:12:25,000
you always did our
income tax returns before.

189
00:12:25,133 --> 00:12:26,500
Don't pass it on to others.

190
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:29,033
You know I only trust you.

191
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:30,700
Alright.

192
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,467
I'll do it myself.

193
00:12:34,967 --> 00:12:36,933
But, Ma, about the wedding...

194
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:37,867
Alright.

195
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,600
Think about it.

196
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:42,700
Next week, Charlie and Princess
will be there.

197
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:45,533
Princess will have
her dress fitting.

198
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:47,033
Pick them up
at the airport.

199
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,033
Spend some time with them.

200
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:51,567
It might change your mind.

201
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:58,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:02,400
You two...

203
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:06,333
You didn't help me
convince Anna to come home.

204
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:09,567
Why are you forcing
her to come to my wedding?

205
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:14,200
Princess,
I'm doing this for you.

206
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:19,200
I don't want Wilson's parents
to think negatively of us.

207
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:22,233
They might think
our family is complicated.

208
00:13:22,433 --> 00:13:24,233
How exactly are
we complicated?

209
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:26,933
We're doing perfectly fine
without Anna here.

210
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,600
Hey, Princess,
don't be like that.

211
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:31,100
Anna is still your sister.

212
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:32,767
Doesn't seem like it.

213
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:35,667
She hasn't been
home in what?

214
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,200
Eight years?

215
00:13:37,300 --> 00:13:38,767
Erin barely remembers
her anymore.

216
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:40,867
Right, Erin?

217
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:42,733
You know, if I were Anna,

218
00:13:42,867 --> 00:13:44,067
I wouldn't want
to go home either

219
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,667
because of that
attitude of yours.

220
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,433
Charlie, Princess,
don't fight at the dinner table.

221
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:51,100
There's nothing wrong
with my attitude.

222
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:53,433
You are the problem.

223
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,200
You guys are too nice.

224
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:57,733
You still treat her
like family.

225
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,067
You keep reaching out

226
00:13:59,167 --> 00:14:01,133
even though
she clearly abandoned us.

227
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:02,533
She doesn't care
about us anymore.

228
00:14:02,667 --> 00:14:03,700
How can you say that?

229
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,133
She's the one solving
our problems about the inn.

230
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:08,200
She fixes everything
even though she's far away.

231
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:11,367
Because Mama tells her to.

232
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:14,633
Other people can help us, Ma.

233
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,300
We don't need her here anymore.

234
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:19,933
It would still be better
if we were all here.

235
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,300
How will that happen, Ma?

236
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:24,133
Dad is gone.

237
00:14:24,267 --> 00:14:26,867
- [ERIN] Princess.
- We'll never be complete again.

238
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,033
- Enough.
- Why?!

239
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,000
I'm telling the truth!

240
00:14:30,167 --> 00:14:31,833
[CHARLIE] Geez,
here we go again!

241
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,100
[HELENA] Enough!

242
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:35,767
Stop arguing.

243
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:37,233
Why, Ma?

244
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:39,067
You know that I'm
telling the truth.

245
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,000
After Papa died--

246
00:14:41,133 --> 00:14:42,100
I said enough!

247
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:49,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:14:56,167 --> 00:15:02,500
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:05,433
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]
[WATER SWOOSHING]

250
00:15:05,567 --> 00:15:06,633
[WATER SPLASHES]

251
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:13,667
[WATER SPLASHES]

252
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:23,167
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

253
00:15:26,233 --> 00:15:33,300
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

254
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:36,733
[GASPS]

255
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:43,133
[BREATH QUIVERING]

256
00:15:43,267 --> 00:15:46,867
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:15:50,233 --> 00:15:54,033
Hey, can you...

258
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:59,367
tone it down with
Princess? She's pregnant.

259
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:02,533
I don't know what's up
with Princess, Auntie.

260
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:04,867
We get along,

261
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:09,367
but it irks me when
she badmouths Anna.

262
00:16:13,367 --> 00:16:15,033
Can you blame her?

263
00:16:17,467 --> 00:16:19,067
It's because of Anna.

264
00:16:20,933 --> 00:16:22,933
Anna just up and left...

265
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,567
without saying anything,

266
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:28,900
didn't tell us where
she was going,

267
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:33,233
and it took ages for her
to show any sign of life.

268
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:37,033
Look, even now,
she hasn't come back.

269
00:16:38,933 --> 00:16:40,900
I don't get Anna either.

270
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:44,900
I've asked her so
many times to tell me...

271
00:16:45,733 --> 00:16:47,933
why she left, but she won't say.

272
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:56,067
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:59,533
But sometimes, I
understand Princess.

274
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:02,100
She was so young back then.

275
00:17:02,967 --> 00:17:05,533
She feels like she lost so much.

276
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:09,267
It's a shame she
didn't take after you.

277
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:11,900
[SOFT MUIC CONTINUES]

278
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,567
Me? Why me?

279
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:16,300
Your strength.

280
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,467
When Uncle passed,
you held it together.

281
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,500
I remember when
he was still alive,

282
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:27,733
he treated you like a queen.

283
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,000
He didn't let you work

284
00:17:29,167 --> 00:17:31,633
because he knew you
came from a wealthy family.

285
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,400
But when he was gone,

286
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,267
you managed everything.

287
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,967
You took on all
the responsibilities

288
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:43,000
without blaming anyone.

289
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,967
I had to. I had to
do it for all of you.

290
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,567
What would've happened
if I had given up?

291
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:52,533
That's why, Auntie...

292
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:57,767
That's why Anna saw that
too, didn't she? She helped you.

293
00:17:57,867 --> 00:18:01,333
She was the one who thought of
turning your house into an inn.

294
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,000
If Princess only knew

295
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:05,867
that Anna made sure she
could finish her studies.

296
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:09,767
It wasn't just Anna.

297
00:18:11,367 --> 00:18:17,133
We all worked hard and
sacrificed to make this grow.

298
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:19,133
Especially you.

299
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:23,700
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

300
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:24,733
[GLASSES CLINK]

301
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:30,467
Alright, finished or not,
pass your papers to the front.

302
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,667
Ms. Sarmiento.

303
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:44,400
- Sir.
- Can I talk to you?

304
00:18:45,767 --> 00:18:47,367
I'll really go to the
principal's office.

305
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:50,033
I have something
important to report to you.

306
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:52,300
If it's about your leaving,

307
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:55,200
Teacher Patty already
told me your plan.

308
00:18:55,400 --> 00:19:00,333
But before you go,
can I ask a favor?

309
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:04,867
While Teacher Thelma
is on maternity leave,

310
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:07,567
can you take over her class?

311
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:11,067
I need you to keep an
eye on Grace Banaag.

312
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:12,867
She's a bit of a problem.

313
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:16,233
She's stubborn, always fighting,

314
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:19,400
and when she does show
up, she's either late or asleep.

315
00:19:19,567 --> 00:19:22,533
I'm counting on you to help her.

316
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,500
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

317
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:27,333
Because of you, Teacher
Thelma gave birth early.

318
00:19:27,433 --> 00:19:30,900
Didn't I tell you not
to join the dance?

319
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:32,733
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

320
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:35,867
Your performance was all
over the place, out of sync.

321
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:37,267
I had to step in and help.

322
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:40,567
Even so, you didn't
have a costume.

323
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:43,033
- You shouldn't have joined.
- Exactly.

324
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:44,533
You shouldn't have joined.

325
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:46,467
You didn't even have a costume.

326
00:19:47,267 --> 00:19:49,433
I said I had a costume!

327
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,733
Really? Then bring it tomorrow

328
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:55,067
- Yeah, bring it tomorrow.
- Sure, bring it.

329
00:19:55,167 --> 00:19:57,367
You don't have
one. You're lying.

330
00:19:57,467 --> 00:19:59,800
Your mom didn't
buy you one, did she?

331
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:01,467
- Liar!
- Liar!

332
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:04,767
That's not true!
My mom bought me one,

333
00:20:04,967 --> 00:20:07,500
at the mall. It was expensive!

334
00:20:08,367 --> 00:20:12,100
Really, Grace? You don't
even have soap at home.

335
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:15,100
You're always dirty and smelly.

336
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:16,233
Yeah.

337
00:20:16,333 --> 00:20:18,900
Maybe Grace isn't
loved by her mom.

338
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,967
She doesn't take care of her.

339
00:20:21,133 --> 00:20:23,433
- Her mom doesn't love her!
- Her mom doesn't love her!

340
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:26,133
That's not true!
My mom loves me!

341
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,233
She takes care of me!

342
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:31,333
Then why doesn't anyone
pick you up after school?

343
00:20:31,467 --> 00:20:34,600
You were probably just
picked up from carabao poop!

344
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,767
[LAUGHING]

345
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:38,633
- Poop!
- Poop!

346
00:20:38,733 --> 00:20:40,700
Where are you going?

347
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:43,633
- Her mom doesn't love her!
- Her mom doesn't love her!

348
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:45,967
- Her mom doesn't love her!
- Stop it!

349
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:48,867
- [THUDS]
- Thank you!

350
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,300
Thank you!
- Oh my--

351
00:20:50,467 --> 00:20:51,533
What's going on here?

352
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:53,767
Ma'am,
Grace was fighting with us.

353
00:20:53,867 --> 00:20:56,667
- Yes, ma'am, Grace started it!
- Yes, ma'am, it was Grace!

354
00:20:58,167 --> 00:20:59,167
Grace Banaag?

355
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:04,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

356
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:09,767
My name is Ms. Anna Sarmiento.

357
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:14,033
I'm the substitute teacher
for Ma'am Thelma Reyes.

358
00:21:14,033 --> 00:21:17,533
Now, I would like to
speak with your parents.

359
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,633
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

360
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,333
But, Teacher...

361
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:22,167
What?

362
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:23,633
Can you not talk to them?

363
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:26,033
I'll just apologize.

364
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:31,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

365
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,067
You know,

366
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,667
you shouldn't apologize
just to get out of trouble.

367
00:21:35,833 --> 00:21:39,067
Do it because you
did something wrong.

368
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:44,533
I still want to speak
with your parents.

369
00:21:44,633 --> 00:21:45,767
Understood?

370
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:49,167
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

371
00:21:49,267 --> 00:21:51,200
Okay, moving forward,

372
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:53,867
I want you to group
yourselves into five.

373
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:56,000
Discuss what you've
learned in the chapter.

374
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:58,167
Then, you will present it to me.

375
00:21:58,867 --> 00:21:59,833
Understood?

376
00:21:59,933 --> 00:22:01,533
- Yes, ma'am.
- Yes, ma'am.

377
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:03,367
Do it then.

378
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,600
Can I join your group?

379
00:22:10,733 --> 00:22:14,600
No, we might get lice
if we let you join our group.

380
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,367
Can I join your group?

381
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:19,300
There are five
of us already.

382
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:23,800
Scion.

383
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:29,300
We don't like you.
Go away.

384
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:38,233
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

385
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:49,433
[KNOCKING]

386
00:22:49,633 --> 00:22:51,067
Good morning, Grace.

387
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,267
Is my class boring?

388
00:22:54,367 --> 00:22:57,500
[KIDS LAUGHING]
No, ma'am.

389
00:22:57,633 --> 00:22:59,133
Shh!

390
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,633
Why aren't you joining
the group work?

391
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,967
Can I just do it
by myself?

392
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:08,267
You think you can
do it alone?

393
00:23:08,367 --> 00:23:09,567
Of course.

394
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:13,167
Get a piece of paper.

395
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,233
Write down everything
you need to do.

396
00:23:27,367 --> 00:23:31,500
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

397
00:23:31,667 --> 00:23:34,100
Can I just memorize it?

398
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,433
Alright.

399
00:23:37,533 --> 00:23:40,033
If you don't want to participate
in today's activity,

400
00:23:40,167 --> 00:23:41,633
you'll get a zero.

401
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:53,167
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

402
00:24:10,033 --> 00:24:17,133
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

403
00:24:48,067 --> 00:24:55,100
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

404
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,167
Pipo!

405
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:04,300
Pipo?

406
00:25:04,433 --> 00:25:06,133
[CHICKEN CUCKOOS]

407
00:25:08,133 --> 00:25:09,233
[CHICKEN CUCKOOS]

408
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,467
[CHICKEN CUCKOOS]

409
00:25:17,567 --> 00:25:18,733
Eat it, Pipo.

410
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:23,567
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

411
00:25:23,733 --> 00:25:25,067
Let's eat, Pa.

412
00:25:28,967 --> 00:25:30,700
Grace, where's my coffee?

413
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,300
[SARAH YAWNS]

414
00:25:33,167 --> 00:25:35,267
My goodness!

415
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:38,467
Didn't I tell you not to bring
your chicken inside the house?

416
00:25:38,633 --> 00:25:39,433
[CHICKEN CUCKOOS]

417
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,067
Pipo is nice, Ma.

418
00:25:42,033 --> 00:25:44,700
If you hadn't won
that chicken at the fair,

419
00:25:44,700 --> 00:25:47,433
I wouldn't have let you
bring it home.

420
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,800
What time is it?

421
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,767
Didn't I tell you
to wake me up at five?

422
00:25:50,867 --> 00:25:52,800
I'm going to be late for work.

423
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:56,500
It's not five yet, Ma.
Pipo hasn't crowed yet.

424
00:25:56,633 --> 00:25:58,467
Damn it, Grace!

425
00:25:58,633 --> 00:26:01,367
You still can't read time?

426
00:26:01,367 --> 00:26:02,967
What are you even
learning at school then?

427
00:26:03,133 --> 00:26:05,733
- I've learned some things, Ma.
- What?

428
00:26:05,833 --> 00:26:08,767
I danced really well
on Teachers' Day, you know.

429
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:10,967
They loved my performance!

430
00:26:11,667 --> 00:26:13,300
Teachers' Day?

431
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:14,667
Is that what you needed
a dress for?

432
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:17,500
It's okay, Ma.
It's already done.

433
00:26:17,667 --> 00:26:20,700
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

434
00:26:20,867 --> 00:26:23,267
But I was still the best
among them.

435
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,633
I take after you.

436
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,000
Shh!

437
00:26:26,133 --> 00:26:27,333
Don't say that.

438
00:26:27,467 --> 00:26:29,433
Don't be like me.

439
00:26:29,567 --> 00:26:31,333
We shouldn't be the same.

440
00:26:31,467 --> 00:26:32,633
Do you understand?

441
00:26:34,667 --> 00:26:36,467
[UTENSILS CLINK, CUP THUDS]

442
00:26:36,633 --> 00:26:37,967
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

443
00:26:38,133 --> 00:26:38,867
Ma...

444
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,300
What is it?
I don't have any money.

445
00:26:41,467 --> 00:26:44,967
No. My teacher just wants
to talk to you.

446
00:26:45,167 --> 00:26:47,733
No way. What did you
do again this time?

447
00:26:47,867 --> 00:26:49,700
Just make something up.
I don't want to.

448
00:26:51,667 --> 00:26:53,467
[CHITO EXHALES DEEPLY]

449
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:54,900
[SARAH] Oh.

450
00:26:55,033 --> 00:26:56,400
Chito!

451
00:26:56,533 --> 00:26:57,867
Where have you been?

452
00:26:58,733 --> 00:27:01,633
Hey, why are you coming
home just now?

453
00:27:02,933 --> 00:27:04,900
- I went to find money.
- Huh?

454
00:27:05,033 --> 00:27:06,067
Here.

455
00:27:07,267 --> 00:27:08,733
For the household expenses.

456
00:27:10,333 --> 00:27:11,667
Let me see.

457
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:15,633
Aww. You're the best, love.

458
00:27:15,767 --> 00:27:18,100
Wow, four thousand.

459
00:27:18,233 --> 00:27:21,500
Grace, serve your uncle food
so he can eat.

460
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:24,500
[CHITO] You're serving me
just rice and soy sauce?

461
00:27:24,633 --> 00:27:25,567
Nothing else?

462
00:27:25,700 --> 00:27:29,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

463
00:27:29,700 --> 00:27:31,667
That's all we have.

464
00:27:31,767 --> 00:27:38,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

465
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:42,067
Is that so?

466
00:27:42,433 --> 00:27:46,667
You should've told me
so we could've bought food.

467
00:27:46,900 --> 00:27:48,200
Don't worry. Hold on.

468
00:27:48,433 --> 00:27:50,533
Go buy some food
at the eatery, okay?

469
00:27:51,133 --> 00:27:53,067
Just buy one order
of adobo, okay?

470
00:27:53,167 --> 00:27:54,033
[GLASS SHATTERS]
Oh!

471
00:27:54,167 --> 00:27:55,267
Son of a--

472
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:59,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

473
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:00,533
Hey.

474
00:28:02,167 --> 00:28:04,567
What's with that glare?

475
00:28:05,233 --> 00:28:06,800
- She's not--
- Be quiet!

476
00:28:09,167 --> 00:28:11,033
You think you're
so tough now, huh?!

477
00:28:11,167 --> 00:28:12,933
Why are you glaring at me?

478
00:28:13,067 --> 00:28:16,100
Do you want me
tp pluck your eyes out?!

479
00:28:16,233 --> 00:28:17,433
[SARAH] Chito. [GASPS]
[THUD]

480
00:28:20,167 --> 00:28:22,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
[SARAH] Grace! Grace!

481
00:28:24,267 --> 00:28:25,767
- [CHITO] You brat!
- Chito!

482
00:28:25,933 --> 00:28:26,767
What?!

483
00:28:27,433 --> 00:28:30,433
Discipline your daughter!
Look how rude she is!

484
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:37,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

485
00:28:47,033 --> 00:28:49,400
A home full of violence.

486
00:28:49,533 --> 00:28:51,333
Grace, what the hell?!
Why is still there no food?!

487
00:28:51,433 --> 00:28:53,200
I'm starving here.
Go prepare something.

488
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:55,167
You almost started a fire.
What happened?!

489
00:28:55,333 --> 00:28:58,467
A love that is
not reciprocated.

490
00:28:58,633 --> 00:29:00,433
I love you, Mama.

491
00:29:00,567 --> 00:29:03,000
You love me too, right?

492
00:29:03,133 --> 00:29:06,033
A sense of compassion
she will find in others.

493
00:29:06,167 --> 00:29:08,200
You should take a shower
every day

494
00:29:08,367 --> 00:29:10,433
so you'll avoid
getting sick.

495
00:29:11,167 --> 00:29:12,833
Grace, tell us.

496
00:29:12,833 --> 00:29:14,200
How did you get that bruise?

497
00:29:15,067 --> 00:29:18,333
Saving Grace: The Untold Story.
